Property.Value: This world configuration demonstrates how to make a world that is as flat as possible. Uses a single biome with custom height and volatility settings. In the world settings all biomes but one have been removed from Biome Groups, only the NormalBiomes group remains with a single biome. Border biomes and Isle biomes list are empty to prevent other biomes from spawning. LandRarity is set to 100 to prevent oceans from spawning. LandFuzzy is set to 0 for smoother terrain. Flat bedrock is enabled. In the biome settings height is 0 and biome volatility is set extremely low for smoother terrain. For this example rivers, canyons, caves and vanilla structures have been disabled via the world settings. Resources (ores, trees etc) have been disabled via the ResourceQueue biome setting.
